{"title": "Thunder and Lightning", "description": "It would be an interesting thing to make a careful study once a year, towards the end of the summer, of the habits and customs of thunder and lightning. Perhaps in this way we should succeed one day in determining the still mysterious nature of these elusive forces. I, for my part, have been engaged upon the task for many years past. It has produced a big accumulation of records, and in this volume I can find room but for a r\u00e9sum\u00e9 of them, as varied as possible.  - Summary by Camille Flammarion", "duration": 24796, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "3363", "name": "Camille Flammarion"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/thunder_lightning_2310_librivox/thunderlighning_2310.jpg", "copyright_year": "1905", "genres": ["Nature", "Astronomy", "Physics & Mechanics", "Earth Sciences"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Amy Gramour"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Amy Gramour"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Rapunzelina"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "CHAPTER I. THE VICTIMS OF LIGHTNING", "readers": [17662], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/thunder_lightning_2310_librivox/thunder_01_flammarion_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1271}, {"section": 2, "title": "CHAPTER II. ATMOSPHERIC ELECTRICITY AND STORM-CLOUDS", "readers": [16395], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/thunder_lightning_2310_librivox/thunder_02_flammarion_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1386}, {"section": 3, "title": "CHAPTER III. THE FLASH AND THE SOUND", "readers": [10159], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/thunder_lightning_2310_librivox/thunder_03_flammarion_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2516}, {"section": 4, "title": "CHAPTER IV. FIREBALLS. Part 1", "readers": [14947], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/thunder_lightning_2310_librivox/thunder_04_flammarion_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1530}, {"section": 5, "title": "CHAPTER IV. FIREBALLS.